result.execSummary:
The defendant Estrada Tito Baldwin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs [Modifiers: Second and Subsequent Offense], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Petition and Order granting defendant release for funeral.  Court allows defendant to be released at 9:00 a.m. and return by 2:00 p.m. on 2-11-16./ds

Court reads-in possession of marijuana charge from May 8th for purposes of sentencing.

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements by counsel.

Court advises the defendant he may not possess a firearm; is to provide a DNA sample and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

COURT ORDERS defendant to serve 12 months at the House of Correction - the first 5 days is straight time - the balance can be with release privileges for the Day Report Program - no objection to electronic monitoring while in the program - and 134 days credit; pay mandatory costs, assessments and surcharges by 2-1-17 or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant and subject to other collection.

- defendant to provide a DNA sample.
